Princeton Beats Pennsylvania 70-58 to Set Up NCAA Playoff Against Harvard

-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 
2011-03-09T02:06:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/princeton-beats-pennsylvania-70-58-to-set-up-ncaa-playoff-against-harvard.html
  Princeton University  beat the
University of Pennsylvania 70-58 to set up a playoff against  Harvard University  for a place in the national men’s college
basketball tournament.  Harvard and Princeton will play March 12 at  Yale
University ’s John J. Lee Amphitheater in  New Haven ,  Connecticut ,
after tying for the Ivy League title. Tip-off is scheduled for 4
p.m. local time.  Princeton made the last of its 23 appearances in the
National Collegiate Athletic Association tournament in 2004.
Harvard has qualified once, in 1946.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  